{"type":"message","id":"23725b52","parentId":"dec9eba0","timestamp":"2026-05-01T19:19:17.521Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to start the server and let Bobby know it's ready. The server listens on port 8791.\n\nBut I realize the architecture is a bit off. The server needs to actually route the text to ME (the main OpenClaw agent) and get back the response. Right now the server just writes to a file and waits.\n\nThe more realistic approach:\n1. The server writes the transcribed text to a file\n2. I need to periodically check that file and respond\n3. Then write the response to the outbox file\n4. The server picks it up and sends the audio back\n\nOR - I could use the OpenClaw Gateway's webhook feature. The server can call a webhook on the gateway when it gets a message, and the gateway processes it.\n\n\nActually, the simplest approach for a self-contained build is to write the text to a file and have me poll it in the background, respond to the outbox, and let the server handle the audio conversion. Let me restructure this more cleanly and get the server running so I can test it out.\n","thinkingSignature":"e892b095411e90d3196f8728a9bd10f95689d987172e7cb90ab5f0b9fbed9712"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ud0e4s3s7762_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/Desktop/Telephone && node server.js &\nsleep 1 && echo \"Server started\"","yieldMs":3000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1025,"output":273,"cacheRead":85440,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86738,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777663147997,"responseId":"06442fac306d4922400daf9e586ace8e"}}
