{"type":"message","id":"7a8c8ab7","parentId":"79f28f23","timestamp":"2026-05-01T19:23:07.515Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The approach of polling and generating responses through a bash script won't work well. The AI response generation needs to go through the proper OpenClaw agent session. Let me think about this differently.\n\nThe cleanest approach:1. User talks on the Telephone page → text sent to server → stored in messages.json2. A separate cron job or background process checks for new messages every few seconds\n3. When new message found, it signals me and I respond via a proper agent session4. My response goes to the server → TTS generated → audio file stored\n5. Browser polls and plays audio\n\nThe issue is the bash script approach with the AI API - it's clunky and won't work well with the OpenClaw session system. \n\nThe real solution here is setting up a cron job that periodically checks for new user messages in messages.json, and when it finds one, fires a signal to me so I can respond in a proper agent turn rather than trying to generate text through a bash script. This way the response generation happens through the normal OpenClaw flow with full session context. a proper subagent that checks messages.json periodically. Actually, let me simplify this and make it work.\n\nHere's the architecture:\n1. `telephone.html` - frontend, speaks to the server\n2. `server.js` - receives transcribed text, stores messages, serves audio\n3. Cron job that polls `messages.json` and triggers me when there's a new user message\n\nLet me delete the bash scripts and set up a cron job properly. The cron job will fire a system event into my session when there are new messages.\n","thinkingSignature":"2d9c059396ba44f0a14e2cfd3863d8629699f028a1e6162e4c08e800c3789ee2"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ihwx24mlxz3w_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"rm ~/Desktop/Telephone/poller.sh ~/Desktop/Telephone/telephone.sh 2>/dev/null; echo \"cleaned\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":624,"output":380,"cacheRead":93952,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":94956,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777663376169,"responseId":"06443090c19c40e2d1f2a184d6ff035e"}}
{"type":"message","id":"394f35df","parentId":"7a8c8ab7","timestamp":"2026-05-01T19:23:07.626Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ihwx24mlxz3w_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"cleaned"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":26,"aggregated":"cleaned","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777663387626}}
{"type":"message","id":"afad9d32","parentId":"394f35df","timestamp":"2026-05-01T19:23:49.083Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me think about the best approach. The Telephone server receives messages and stores them. I need a way for Dean to get notified and respond. \n\nOptions:\n1. A cron job that polls for new messages every few seconds - not great\n2. A dedicated script that runs as a LaunchAgent\n3. Hook into the existing OpenClaw system\n\nActually the cleanest approach is:\n1. Server stores messages in messages.json\n2. Bobby's main session is what responds\n3. Bobby sends a voice message through Telephone → server stores it\n4. I get notified (via cron or manual check) → generate response → post back\n\nBut Bobby wants it to feel real-time and like voice mode on ChatGPT. So there's a responsiveness issue.\n \nI think a dedicated background script running as a LaunchAgent makes the most sense here. It can continuously poll the server for new messages, pull context from the main session, and post Dean responses back in real-time without relying on Bobby to trigger anything.\n","thinkingSignature":"88639fd33b5563101ba2bfe21621246c5cac63ca1e28ac66c3017a6f1ac2d320"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\nNow the key piece — a background runner that watches for your messages and generates Dean responses. Let me write a proper one:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_aggvz6t3x84o_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n/**\n * Telephone — Dean Response Generator\n * Watches for new user messages, generates responses, posts audio back\n */\n\nconst http = require('http');\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst path = require('path');\nconst { execSync } = require('child_process');\n\nconst SERVER = 'http://localhost:8791';\nconst STATE_FILE = path.join(__dirname, '.last_check');\nconst MESSAGES_FILE = path.join(__dirname, 'messages.json');\nconst AUDIO_DIR = path.join(__dirname, 'audio');\n\nconst CHECK_INTERVAL = 3000; // ms between polls\n\nif (!fs.existsSync(AUDIO_DIR)) fs.mkdirSync(AUDIO_DIR, { recursive: true });\n\n// Load last check time\nlet lastCheck = 0;\nif (fs.existsSync(STATE_FILE)) {\n  try { lastCheck = parseInt(fs.readFileSync(STATE_FILE, 'utf8')) || 0; } catch(e) {}\n}\n\nfunction saveLastCheck(ts) {\n  fs.writeFileSync(STATE_FILE, String(ts));\n}\n\nfunction getNewMessages() {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    http.get(`${SERVER}/messages?since=${lastCheck}`, (res) => {\n      let data = '';\n      res.on('data', chunk => data += chunk);\n      res.on('end', () => {\n        try {\n          const parsed = JSON.parse(data);\n          resolve(parsed.messages || []);\n        } catch(e) { resolve([]); }\n      });\n    }).on('error', () => resolve([]));\n  });\n}\n\nfunction postReply(text) {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const postData = JSON.stringify({ text, fromDean: true });\n    const req = http.request({\n      hostname: 'localhost',\n      port: 8791,\n      path: '/reply',\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json', 'Content-Length': Buffer.byteLength(postData) }\n    }, (res) => {\n      let data = '';\n      res.on('data', c => data += c);\n      res.on('end', () => { try { resolve(JSON.parse(data)); } catch(e) { resolve({ ok: false }); } });\n    });\n    req.on('error', () => resolve({ ok: false }));\n    req.write(postData);\n    req.end();\n  });\n}\n\nfunction textToAudio(text, callback) {\n  const ts = Date.now();\n  const mp3Path = path.join(AUDIO_DIR, `reply_${ts}.mp3`);\n  const aiffPath = `/tmp/dean_telephone_${ts}.aiff`;\n\n  try {\n    // Clean text for say command\n    const clean = text.replace(/[\"\\\\]/g, '').replace(/\\n+/g, ' ').replace(/\\s+/g, ' ').trim();\n    if (!clean) { callback(null); return; }\n\n    execSync(`say \"${clean}\" -o ${aiffPath} 2>/dev/null`, { stdio: 'pipe' });\n    execSync(`ffmpeg -i ${aiffPath} \"${mp3Path}\" -y 2>/dev/null`, { stdio: 'pipe' });\n    fs.unlinkSync(aiffPath);\n\n    callback(mp3Path);\n  } catch(e) {\n    console.error('TTS error:', e.message);\n    callback(null);\n  }\n}\n\nasync function generateResponse(userText) {\n  // Load conversation history from messages.json\n  let history = [];\n  if (fs.existsSync(MESSAGES_FILE)) {\n    try { history = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(MESSAGES_FILE, 'utf8')); } catch(e) {}\n  }\n\n  // Build context string from history\n  const contextParts = history.slice(-10).map(m => {\n    const speaker = m.from === 'dean' ? 'Dean' : 'Bobby';\n    return `${speaker}: ${m.text}`;\n  }).join('\\n');\n\n  const prompt = `You are Dean the Machine 🤖🦞, Bobby's main AI assistant. Bobby just spoke to you via Telephone (a voice chat app). Keep responses SHORT — 1 to 3 sentences max. Conversational, casual, like talking to a friend. Under 30 seconds of speech when read aloud.\n\n${contextParts ? `Recent conversation:\\n${contextParts}\\n` : ''}\nBobby: ${userText}\nDean:`;\n\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    try {\n      const result = execSync(\n        `curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8787/v1/chat/completions \\\n          -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n          -d '${JSON.stringify({ model: \"minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7\", messages: [{ role: \"user\", content: prompt }], max_tokens: 150 })}' 2>/dev/null`,\n        { encoding: 'utf8', maxDuration: 30000 }\n      );\n      const parsed = JSON.parse(result);\n      const text = parsed.choices?.[0]?.message?.content?.trim();\n      resolve(text || \"I'm here, Bobby. What's up?\");\n    } catch(e) {\n      resolve(\"I'm here, Bobby. What's up?\");\n    }\n  });\n}\n\nasync function handleMessages() {\n  const messages = await getNewMessages();\n\n  if (messages.length === 0) return;\n\n  for (const msg of messages) {\n    if (msg.from !== 'user') continue;\n\n    console.log(`[Telephone] Bobby said: ${msg.text}`);\n\n    // Generate response\n    const replyText = await generateResponse(msg.text);\n    console.log(`[Telephone] Dean says: ${replyText}`);\n\n    // Convert to audio and post\n    textToAudio(replyText, (mp3Path) => {\n      if (mp3Path) {\n        const audioFile = `/audio/${path.basename(mp3Path)}`;\n        postReply(replyText).then(() => {\n          console.log(`[Telephone] Audio reply posted: ${audioFile}`);\n        });\n      }\n    });\n\n    // Update last check\n    if (msg.timestamp > lastCheck) {\n      lastCheck = msg.timestamp;\n      saveLastCheck(lastCheck);\n    }\n  }\n}\n\n// Main loop\nasync function run() {\n  console.log('[Telephone] Dean is listening...');\n  while (true) {\n    await handleMessages();\n    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, CHECK_INTERVAL));\n  }\n}\n\nrun().catch(console.error);","path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/dean.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":116,"output":1633,"cacheRead":94528,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":96277,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777663387628,"responseId":"0644309b2f081fad01cf8e4144d536a3"}}
