{"type":"message","id":"9063225f","parentId":"a7d5cbc8","timestamp":"2026-05-01T19:37:38.763Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me rebuild the Telephone app with a different approach. Instead of using the Web Speech API in the browser (which doesn't work well on localhost in Safari), I'll:\n\n1. Use MediaRecorder to capture audio from the browser\n2. Send the audio blob to the server\n3. On the server, use macOS native tools to transcribe - either:\n   - `asr` (Apple Speech Recognition command line tool)\n   - Or `say` with a different approach\n   - Or use a local transcription approach\n\nActually, macOS has `asr` (Apple Speech Recognition) but it's not a simple command-line tool. Let me think about what's available.\n   \nI'm realizing the built-in `say` command can't transcribe, so I need to use macOS's native Speech framework instead. I can write a native Node.js module using the Speech framework, or leverage macOS's system-level transcription services directly. I could also try the macOS `speechsynthesis` command-line tool, though I'm not certain about its availability. Let me check what tools are actually available on the system first.","thinkingSignature":"7a0c2dcc97cd5f74762ea1e2cf6f274c750bca6338ddf8dc5a7558772ced49c3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7t9idpzxapyq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"which asr 2>/dev/null; which rev 2>/dev/null; say \"test\" 2>/dev/null && echo \"say works\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":101604,"output":280,"cacheRead":224,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":102108,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777664248427,"responseId":"064433f9d81dfb3cd56dc4c9dd8eb1cf"}}
