{"type":"message","id":"866f5f09","parentId":"59179d38","timestamp":"2026-05-01T19:37:46.790Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, `say` works and the system has `asr` and `rev` for speech recognition. Let me check if we can use the Mac's native speech recognition from the command line. The `asr` command is the Apple Speech Recognition tool. Let me see if it can be used for real-time transcription.\n\nActually, let me try a simpler approach:\n1. Record audio in the browser using MediaRecorder (webm format)\n2. Send the audio blob to the server\n3. Server uses `afconvert` + a transcription method to get the text\n\nFor Mac native transcription, I could try:\n- Using the `asr` tool (Apple Speech Recognition)\n\n\n- Or the `rev` command\n\nLet me first check if `rev` can handle audio files and what formats it supports.","thinkingSignature":"aa63c59df33b89b1dcfabd672361c7467e1d71b6cb7d3bea4daddee9176318fe"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wrecmba3alum_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"rev --help 2>&1 | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":84,"output":200,"cacheRead":101824,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":102108,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777664264386,"responseId":"06443408cfa3a416ab3eee22e0e73ad4"}}
