{"type":"message","id":"b49610be","parentId":"1eb43ccf","timestamp":"2026-05-01T19:47:18.042Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby is still saying the links aren't working. The inline button didn't work either apparently. \n\nLet me think about this differently. The issue might be that Telegram on his iPhone isn't showing links as clickable. Let me try using a proper Telegram bot message format that forces a hyperlink.\n\nActually, let me check if the issue is with how OpenClaw's message tool sends links in Telegram. \n\nOne thing I can try is using `message action=send` with a Markdown-formatted message where the link appears as a proper hyperlink in Telegram.\n\nActually, the issue might be that in Telegram, for a URL to be clickable, it just needs to be sent as a plain URL (not in a code block, not mixed with text in certain ways). \n\n\nI've tried plain URLs and formatted links, but Bobby says neither works. The inline button I sent might be the real solution here — that should definitely show as a tappable button if the format is correct. Maybe the problem is that he's not seeing the button at all, or it's not being formatted properly on his end. Let me verify the button format is actually correct. I think the real issue might be that Bobby's iPhone Telegram app isn't rendering these URLs as clickable links at all. Let me try using the message tool with a markdown link to see if that makes a difference.\n","thinkingSignature":"fa25b41e6525ed0673cf64f9e41561abbd8bd4007b5736c834f32b309dd80ea1"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xf6td03iosli_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":109071,"output":311,"cacheRead":192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":109574,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777664821151,"respo