{"type":"message","id":"c4e5ce7b","parentId":"7cfb979a","timestamp":"2026-05-01T19:48:42.928Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me try a different approach. Looking at the message tool, it has `presentation.blocks` with buttons type. But the issue is Bobby needs raw hyperlinks that are clickable in Telegram chat.\n\nLet me try sending a message with an inline keyboard button via the `reply_markup` approach that Telegram supports. The message tool has a `presentation` parameter that might support this.\n\nActually, looking at the message tool params more carefully, I see `presentation` with blocks including buttons. Let me try sending with a URL button. But the issue is the text content of the message itself needs to be formatted as a hyperlink.\n\nFor Telegram, when you want a clickable hyperlink in a plain text message (not with buttons), the text needs to be formatted with HTML or Markdown. The message tool should handle this.\n\n\nI'm noticing a discrepancy in the port configuration - the config shows 18789 but the summary indicates 8787. Looking at the channels.telegram config section, I'm trying to understand how the message tool is formatting messages to create those clickable hyperlinks, since the raw URL approach isn't working.\n","thinkingSignature":"4c924d6d8773d2646b8e971c1a12a693c681858c749d2e698a6d25092e843b4b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_73okpcdoqzsc_1","name":"gateway","arguments":{"action":"config.get","path":"channels.telegram"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":51391,"output":259,"cacheRead":128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":51778,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777664915181,"responseId":"0644369390c5d07ad5e223f04851cfbb"}}
