{"type":"message","id":"736d4130","parentId":"4139334e","timestamp":"2026-05-01T19:49:06.652Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the raw URL `http://localhost:8790/telephone.html` gets sent as a plain text message via the Telegram bot API, but it's NOT clickable. This means Telegram doesn't auto-link http://localhost URLs because localhost is a reserved hostname that can't be accessed from the public internet. Even if Bobby's phone is on the same WiFi, Telegram might not treat it as a valid clickable URL.\n\nThe solution is to use the Tailscale URL (https://bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net) which is already in the allowed origins and is accessible from anywhere. Let me try that.\n","thinkingSignature":"edbbab883b7240486e371162303919567a4d9db645254d511556a8be4e3266c0"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_v7pwiar9cy0l_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s https://api.telegram.org/bot$(cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d['channels']['telegram']['accounts']['default']['botToken'])\")/sendMessage -d \"chat_id=8212808444&text=https://bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net/telephone.html&parse_mode=HTML\" 2>&1 | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":348,"output":259,"cacheRead":74560,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75167,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777664941164,"responseId":"064436ad19da73365fc495d7f07e5acd"}}
