{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"telegram:8212808444\",\n  \"message_id\": \"24117\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"24114\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"sender\": \"B G\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-05-01 15:49 EDT\",\n  \"has_reply_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"B G (8212808444)\",\n  \"id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"name\": \"B G\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"Dean the Machine 🤖🦞\",\n  \"body\": \"https://bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net/telephone.html\"\n}\n```","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"63773bd0","parentId":"8f970979","timestamp":"2026-05-01T19:49:57.128Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"7a9321ef","parentId":"63773bd0","timestamp":"2026-05-01T19:50:12.211Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the inline button format works! The issue was that when I was sending plain URLs or even formatted markdown in the message tool, Telegram wasn't rendering them as clickable links. But the inline button with a URL renders as a tappable button.\n\nSo now I need to remember: for clickable links in Telegram, use the inline button format in the presentation block. NOT markdown link format, not plain text URLs.\n\nLet me update my rules in TOOLS.md to remember this.\n","thinkingSignature":"a2b08c7066194da65cbdd8568a2ebafd9ad9f9774ba30fe55ba6a5a51125fb1f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_sqxoj3l6r083_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"edits":[{"newText":"### Message Formatting Rules (Telegram)\n- **ALL links must be sent as inline buttons** — NOT markdown, NOT plain text URLs\n  - Use `presentation: {\"blocks\": [{\"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [{\"label\": \"text\", \"url\": \"https://...\", \"style\": \"primary\"}]}]}`\n  - Plain URLs or markdown `[text](url)` will NOT render as clickable links\n  - Example — always use this format:\n  ```\n  message tool with:\n  message: \"Tap the link\"\n  presentation: {\"blocks\": [{\"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [{\"label\": \"Open Page\", \"url\": \"https://bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net/telephone.html\", \"style\": \"primary\"}]}]}\n  ```","oldText":"### Message Formatting Rules (Telegram)\n- **ALL links must be clickable:** Use `[text](url)` markdown format, NEVER plain URLs\n  - ✅ Correct: `[Fill out the questionnaire](http://localhost:8790/questionnaire.html)`\n  - ❌ Wrong: `http://localhost:8790/questionnaire.html` or `here's the link: http://...`\n  - This applies to EVERY link — local URLs, web links, everything"}],"path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace/TOOLS.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":56381,"output":444,"cacheRead":320,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57145,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777664997128,"responseId":"064436e595d6a65684c232899f057cf4"}}
{"type":"message","id":"c1f2430f","parentId":"7a9321ef","timestamp":"2026-05-01T19:50:12.409Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_sqxoj3l6r083_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"error\",\n  \"tool\": \"edit\",\n  \"error\": \"Could not find the exact text in /Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace/TOOLS.md. The old text must match exactly including all whitespace and newlines.\\nCurrent file contents:\\n# TOOLS.md - Local Notes\\n\\nSkills define _how_ tools work. This file is for _your_ specifics — the stuff that's unique to your setup.\\n\\n## What Goes Here\\n\\nThings like:\\n\\n- Camera names and locations\\n- SSH hosts and aliases\\n- Preferred voices for TTS\\n- Speaker/room names\\n- Device nicknames\\n- Anything environment-specific\\n\\n## Examples\\n\\n```markdown\\n### Cameras\\n\\n- living-room → Main area, 180° wide angle\\n- front-door → Entrance, motion-triggered\\n\\n### SSH\\n\\n- home-server → 192.168.1.100, user: admin\\n\\n### TTS\\n\\n- Preferred voice: \\\"Nova\\\" (warm, slightly British)\\n- Default speaker: Kitchen HomePod\\n```\\n\\n## Why Separate?\\n\\nSkills are shared. Your setup is yours. Keeping them apart means you can update skills without losing your notes, and share skills without leaking your infrastructure.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Email (\\n... (truncated)\"\n}"}],"details":{"status":"error","tool":"edit","error":"Could not find the exact text in /Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace/TOOLS.md. The old text must match exactly including all whitespace and newlines.\nCurrent file contents:\n# TOOLS.md - Local Notes\n\nSkills define _how_ tools work. This file is for _your_ specifics — the stuff that's unique to your setup.\n\n## What Goes Here\n\nThings like:\n\n- Camera names and locations\n- SSH hosts and aliases\n- Preferred voices for TTS\n- Speaker/room names\n- Device nicknames\n- Anything environment-specific\n\n## Examples\n\n```markdown\n### Cameras\n\n- living-room → Main area, 180° wide angle\n- front-door → Entrance, motion-triggered\n\n### SSH\n\n- home-server → 192.168.1.100, user: admin\n\n### TTS\n\n- Preferred voice: \"Nova\" (warm, slightly British)\n- Default speaker: Kitchen HomePod\n```\n\n## Why Separate?\n\nSkills are shared. Your setup is yours. Keeping them apart means you can update skills without losing your notes, and share skills without leaking your infrastructure.\n\n---\n\n### Email (\n... (truncated)"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777665012409}}
