{"type":"message","id":"bc269a30","parentId":"b30b6b12","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:09:45.550Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The HTTP server is running on port 8790. The issue is that Tailscale serve isn't set up, so the `bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net` domain doesn't route to the local HTTP server. I need to either:\n\n1. Set up tailscale serve\n2. Or use another tunneling approach\n\nLet me check if there's a way to expose the service via Tailscale. With Tailscale, I can use `tailscale serve` to expose local services.\n\nBut actually, I should check what worked before when the link WAS clickable. The earlier link `https://bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net/telephone.html` was actually sent and was clickable according to Bobby. So the domain IS registered with Tailscale and the HTTPS works. \n\nThe real problem is that the HTTP server was bound to IPv6 only (`:::8790`) while Tailscale serve expects IPv4. I need to start the HTTP server explicitly on IPv4 with `-h 0.0.0.0` so Tailscale can route traffic to it.\n","thinkingSignature":"0fb29cd3745250408bf15dd68256ce60797b857353bfb10f7917647dcd0e4ca7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_495uckw1nezo_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"pkill -f \"http.server 8790\" 2>/dev/null; sleep 1 && cd ~/Desktop/Telephone && python3 -m http.server 8790 --bind 0.0.0.0 > ~/.openclaw/logs/telephone-http.log 2>&1 &\nsleep 1 && lsof -i :8790 | grep LISTEN"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":259,"output":337,"cacheRead":60672,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61268,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777666179534,"responseId":"06443b836983dac115ff7228a276cb71"}}
