{"type":"message","id":"ccc80f34","parentId":"57a4e26e","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:11:25.415Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9ow9lzl048lm_1","toolName":"image","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The screen shows a chat with two message bubbles:\n\n- “Try this link:” with timestamp 4:10 PM\n- “No follow-up needed from me.” with timestamp 4:10 PM\n\nThere is no visible clickable link or button shown in the image."}],"details":{"model":"openai-codex/gpt-5.5","image":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/media/inbound/file_246---fbd4483d-dea0-478a-8fc2-6f12bdd8ac76.jpg","attempts":[]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777666285415}}
{"type":"message","id":"a477f86a","parentId":"ccc80f34","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:11:33.364Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby's right - the presentation blocks with buttons weren't showing up as visual buttons in Telegram. The message just showed as \"Try this link:\" with no button. That's why he couldn't click anything.\n\nThe issue is the `presentation` format isn't rendering as buttons in Telegram. Looking at the message tool docs, `presentation.blocks.buttons` should work for inline buttons, but apparently it's not working.\n\nWait - but in previous messages, the button DID work. Let me look at what was different. In one case I sent the `<a href>` HTML which DID show as a clickable link (with entities). But the presentation blocks aren't rendering.\n\nActually looking at the image result: \"Try this link:\" with timestamp 4:10 PM and \"No follow-up needed from me.\" with timestamp 4:10 PM - but no button visible. \n\nSo the button format isn't rendering at all. The `<a href>` HTML approach worked much better since it created an actual clickable text link with proper URL entities in Telegram. I should go back to that method instead of relying on the presentation blocks format.\n","thinkingSignature":"665f677981afc65c45c7d15e2448e0eb06c42383d3aa8febc1ea87de0641455b"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nYou're right, I'm sorry. The button format isn't showing up — Telegram isn't rendering it as a clickable button.\n\nLet me try the HTML link format that worked before:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ceihx5p2o4qk_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"TOKEN=$(cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d['channels']['telegram']['accounts']['default']['botToken'])\")\n\ncurl -s \"https://api.telegram.org/bot${TOKEN}/sendMessage\" \\\n  -d 'chat_id=8212808444&text=<a href=\"https://bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net/telephone.html\">Open Telephone</a>&parse_mode=HTM