{"type":"message","id":"1996620e","parentId":"d6f000db","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:13:18.242Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Tailscale serve is working correctly. The issue isn't with the server - it's that the inline keyboard buttons aren't rendering in the Telegram message on Bobby's phone.\n\nLooking at the buildInlineKeyboard code again:\n```javascript\nfunction buildInlineKeyboard(buttons) {\n\tif (!buttons?.length) return;\n\tconst rows = buttons.map((row) => row.filter((button) => button?.text && button?.callback_data).map((button) => Object.assign({\n\t\ttext: button.text,\n\t\tcallback_data: button.callback_data\n\t}, button.style ? { style: button.style } : {}))).filter((row) => row.length > 0);\n\n\n```\n\nThe function only accepts buttons with `callback_data` fields, not URL buttons. So the Telegram plugin doesn't support URL buttons at all through the message tool - I need to use the Telegram Bot API directly instead.\n\nLooking at the curl output, the HTML link with `parse_mode=HTML` sent earlier did include a `text_link` entity, so that approach worked for creating clickable links. That's the real solution here - I should use the Bot API directly with HTML-formatted messages rather than relying on the message tool's button formatting.\n\n```\n","thinkingSignature":"092d0475d89e8b98440d2d2d9a976c9b5d7b111799a48f0daecb7ed70ab1f34c"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nI see the issue — the message tool's button format doesn't support URL buttons. Only `callback_data` works, which isn't clickable. \n\nThe HTML link approach works though. Let me send you the link properly now:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_u9dlhnb9xmxl_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"TOKEN=$(cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d['channels']['telegram']['accounts']['default']['botToken'])\")\n\ncurl -s \"https://api.telegram.org/bot${TOKEN}/sendMessage\" \\\n  -d 'chat_id=8212808444&text=<a href=\"https://bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net/telephone.html\">Open Telephone</a>&parse_mode=HTML&disable_web_page_preview=false' 2>&1 | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print('ok:', d['ok'], 'entities:', d.get('result',{}).get('entities',[]))\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":193,"output":477,"cacheRead":65216,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65886,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777666391044,"responseId":"06443c57af3ad3299039b66f99bee2da"}}
