{"type":"message","id":"a51b8321","parentId":"b56dd1fd","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:13:26.397Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The HTML link with `text_link` entity shows it IS being sent correctly. But Bobby says it's not showing as clickable. Let me think about this differently.\n\nMaybe the issue is with the Telegram app on his phone specifically. Or maybe the message tool IS rendering the presentation blocks correctly but something in the middle is stripping it.\n\nWait - let me look at the screenshot again. The screenshot shows TWO messages:\n1. \"Try this link:\"\n2. \"No follow-up needed from me.\"\n\nBut I didn't send a message saying \"No follow-up needed from me.\" That message must have come from somewhere else - maybe a previous session or another agent? That message has entities that show it was formatted as a link but Bobby can't click on it.\n \nHold on - Bobby's actually confirming the links ARE working in those last four messages. He's saying he can click them. So the issue is something else entirely - maybe a loading problem or something specific to that \"site can't be reached\" error he mentioned earlier.\n","thinkingSignature":"8b9bbfc050a586f0f99171f923162e5352d408747e089d55b2ead4018cc70086"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_027j898gh9wj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"TOKEN=$(cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d['channels']['telegram']['accounts']['default']['botToken'])\")\n\n# Get the last few messages to see what's being sent\ncurl -s \"https://api.telegram.org/bot${TOKEN}/getUpdates\" -d \"limit=5&offset=-1\" 2>&1 | python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\nd = json.load(sys.stdin)\nfor m in d.get('result', []):\n    msg = m.get('message', {})\n    text = msg.get('text', '')\n    ent = msg.get('entities', [])\n    print(f'Msg {msg.get(\\\"message_id\\\")}: {repr(text[:50])} | entities: {ent}')\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider"