{"type":"message","id":"9507ead7","parentId":"9ff1ad20","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:13:33.089Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me try a completely different approach. Let me just send the link using the HTML method directly and see if it works. I know from my curl tests that the HTML `<a href>` format creates a `text_link` entity, which should be clickable.\n\nLet me also try using the Telegram bot API to edit the existing message to add the link button format.\n\nActually, let me just send it via curl using the HTML method and see if Bobby gets it as a clickable link. Based on my earlier tests, `parse_mode=HTML` with `<a href=\"...\">text</a>` creates entities with `type: \"text_link\"` which SHOULD be clickable.\n\n\nI'll test the HTML format one more time with the message tool to verify the entities are actually being created correctly and see what happens on the Telegram side.\n","thinkingSignature":"9594bafa2dc6ac124eb24138813269c15973e3850e4639c0fc891abe8e882175"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9z26gzmpxqjd_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"TOKEN=$(cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d['channels']['telegram']['accounts']['default']['botToken'])\")\n\n# Send as HTML hyperlink\ncurl -s \"https://api.telegram.org/bot${TOKEN}/sendMessage\" \\\n  -d 'chat_id=8212808444&text=Open Telephone: <a href=\"https://bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net/telephone.html\">tap here</a>&parse_mode=HTML' 2>&1 | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(json.dumps(d.get('result',{}).get('entities',[]), indent=2))\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":340,"output":357,"cacheRead":65536,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66233,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777666406931,"responseId":"06443c67edcb1f4546066a52986fba0b"}}
