{"type":"message","id":"d3f0ea94","parentId":"11ae61fc","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:15:15.451Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So Bobby CAN see clickable links! The messages show:\n- Blue underlined \"Open Telephone\" links (HTML format)\n- Green button-style link previews labeled \"Open Telephone\" with an arrow icon\n\nSo the system IS working. The issue earlier was that some messages I sent didn't have the clickable formatting, and Bobby may not have been tapping on the right ones.\n\nThe green buttons with the arrow icon - those are the inline keyboard buttons I was trying to send. They ARE showing up and ARE clickable.\n\nSo my current approach IS working. The problem earlier was:\n1. When I sent plain text \"Try this link:\" - no link\n2. When I used the button format - it showed as a green bar with an arrow icon and was clickable\n3. When I sent HTML `<a href=\"...\">text</a>` - it showed as blue underlined text and was clickable\n\nBobby can see them! So everything is working now. I need to just consistently use the HTML format for links, and they will appear as clickable blue links.\n\nLet me confirm the URL is working and move on.\n","thinkingSignature":"937286d7b01161926e1395cf5d333fa41368a892d7312cdb0e27cdf007099e3e"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThe system IS working — you have blue clickable links and green button bars. That's exactly what it's supposed to look like.\n\nThe problem earlier was inconsistency on my end. Now I know the rule: **HTML `<a href=\"url\">text</a>`** = blue clickable link, and **inline keyboard buttons** = green button bar. Both work.\n\nNow let's test the Telephone app. Does the link open and does the mic button work?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":210,"output":322,"cacheRead":74496,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75028,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777666