{"type":"message","id":"49918f6e","parentId":"967ee848","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:19:16.473Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the problem. The whisper transcription is returning \"Could not transcribe\" because there's an issue with the audio being sent. Looking at the curl command in dean.js, there's also a syntax error with the shell command — the `()` characters in the curl command are being interpreted by the shell. \n\nThe core issue is:\n1. \"Could not transcribe\" — whisper is not getting valid audio\n2. The system is treating silence/no audio as \"Could not transcribe\" and Dean keeps responding with \"I'm here Bobby, what's up?\"\n3. There's also a syntax error in the curl command due to the emoji characters `🤖🦞` being passed through the shell\n\n\n4. The microphone on the MacBook Air isn't capturing audio properly when accessed from the iPhone browser, so I need to test the speech recognition directly to see if the issue is with the audio stream itself.\n","thinkingSignature":"d188a5a1ff884f1ef01604c5a61d77cb85f8556104ca5ffc1d0f8f63b4c78c88"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xrvlnm45z1eu_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/Desktop/Telephone/dean.js | head -80"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2555,"output":218,"cacheRead":74272,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77045,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777666753557,"responseId":"06443dc1fe4b5b24193aa9df26215340"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5bf686d9","parentId":"49918f6e","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:19:16.518Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_xrvlnm45z1eu_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n/**\n * Telephone — Dean Response Generator\n * Watches for new user messages, generates responses, posts audio back\n */\n\nconst http = require('http');\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst path = require('path');\nconst { execSync } = require('child_process');\n\nconst SERVER = 'http://localhost:8791';\nconst STATE_FILE = path.join(__dirname, '.last_check');\nconst MESSAGES_FILE = path.join(__dirname, 'messages.json');\nconst AUDIO_DIR = path.join(__dirname, 'audio');\n\nconst CHECK_INTERVAL = 3000; // ms between polls\n\nif (!fs.existsSync(AUDIO_DIR)) fs.mkdirSync(AUDIO_DIR, { recursive: true });\n\n// Load last check time\nlet lastCheck = 0;\nif (fs.existsSync(STATE_FILE)) {\n  try { lastCheck = parseInt(fs.readFileSync(STATE_FILE, 'utf8')) || 0; } catch(e) {}\n}\n\nfunction saveLastCheck(ts) {\n  fs.writeFileSync(STATE_FILE, String(ts));\n}\n\nfunction getNewMessages() {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    http.get(`${SERVER}/messages?since=${lastCheck}`, (res) => {\n      let data = '';\n      res.on('data', chunk => data += chunk);\n      res.on('end', () => {\n        try {\n          const parsed = JSON.parse(data);\n          resolve(parsed.messages || []);\n        } catch(e) { resolve([]); }\n      });\n    }).on('error', () => resolve([]));\n  });\n}\n\nfunction postReply(text) {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const postData = JSON.stringify({ text, fromDean: true });\n    const req = http.request({\n      hostname: 'localhost',\n      port: 8791,\n      path: '/reply',\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json', 'Content-Length': Buffer.byteLength(postData) }\n    }, (res) => {\n      let data = '';\n      res.on('data', c => data += c);\n      res.on('end', () => { try { resolve(JSON.parse(data)); } catch(e) { resolve({ ok: false }); } });\n    });\n    req.on('error', () => resolve({ ok: false }));\n    req.write(postData);\n    req.end();\n  });\n}\n\nfunction textToAudio(text, callback) {\n  const ts = Date.now();\n  const mp3Path = path.join(AUDIO_DIR, `reply_${ts}.mp3`);\n  const aiffPath = `/tmp/dean_telephone_${ts}.aiff`;\n\n  try {\n    // Clean text for say command\n    const clean = text.replace(/[\"\\\\]/g, '').replace(/\\n+/g, ' ').replace(/\\s+/g, ' ').trim();\n    if (!clean) { callback(null); return; }\n\n    execSync(`say \"${clean}\" -o ${aiffPath} 2>/dev/null`, { stdio: 'pipe' });\n    execSync(`ffmpeg -i ${aiffPath} \"${mp3Path}\" -y 2>/dev/null`, { stdio: 'pipe' });\n    fs.unlinkSync(aiffPath);\n\n    callback(mp3Path);"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":9,"aggregated":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n/**\n * Telephone — Dean Response Generator\n * Watches for new user messages, generates responses, posts audio back\n */\n\nconst http = require('http');\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst path = require('path');\nconst { execSync } = require('child_process');\n\nconst SERVER = 'http://localhost:8791';\nconst STATE_FILE = path.join(__dirname, '.last_check');\nconst MESSAGES_FILE = path.join(__dirname, 'messages.json');\nconst AUDIO_DIR = path.join(__dirname, 'audio');\n\nconst CHECK_INTERVAL = 3000; // ms between polls\n\nif (!fs.existsSync(AUDIO_DIR)) fs.mkdirSync(AUDIO_DIR, { recursive: true });\n\n// Load last check time\nlet lastCheck = 0;\nif (fs.existsSync(STATE_FILE)) {\n  try { lastCheck = parseInt(fs.readFileSync(STATE_FILE, 'utf8')) || 0; } catch(e) {}\n}\n\nfunction saveLastCheck(ts) {\n  fs.writeFileSync(STATE_FILE, String(ts));\n}\n\nfunction getNewMessages() {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    http.get(`${SERVER}/messages?since=${lastCheck}`, (res) => {\n      let data = '';\n      res.on('data', chunk => data += chunk);\n      res.on('end', () => {\n        try {\n          const parsed = JSON.parse(data);\n          resolve(parsed.messages || []);\n        } catch(e) { resolve([]); }\n      });\n    }).on('error', () => resolve([]));\n  });\n}\n\nfunction postReply(text) {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const postData = JSON.stringify({ text, fromDean: true });\n    const req = http.request({\n      hostname: 'localhost',\n      port: 8791,\n      path: '/reply',\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json', 'Content-Length': Buffer.byteLength(postData) }\n    }, (res) => {\n      let data = '';\n      res.on('data', c => data += c);\n      res.on('end', () => { try { resolve(JSON.parse(data)); } catch(e) { resolve({ ok: false }); } });\n    });\n    req.on('error', () => resolve({ ok: false }));\n    req.write(postData);\n    req.end();\n  });\n}\n\nfunction textToAudio(text, callback) {\n  const ts = Date.now();\n  const mp3Path = path.join(AUDIO_DIR, `reply_${ts}.mp3`);\n  const aiffPath = `/tmp/dean_telephone_${ts}.aiff`;\n\n  try {\n    // Clean text for say command\n    const clean = text.replace(/[\"\\\\]/g, '').replace(/\\n+/g, ' ').replace(/\\s+/g, ' ').trim();\n    if (!clean) { callback(null); return; }\n\n    execSync(`say \"${clean}\" -o ${aiffPath} 2>/dev/null`, { stdio: 'pipe' });\n    execSync(`ffmpeg -i ${aiffPath} \"${mp3Path}\" -y 2>/dev/null`, { stdio: 'pipe' });\n    fs.unlinkSync(aiffPath);\n\n    callback(mp3Path);","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777666756518}}
{"type":"message","id":"b156bd9b","parentId":"5bf686d9","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:19:20.422Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is clear now. Looking at the dean.js code, it's using the `execSync` with a shell command that has a syntax error due to the special characters (like `🤖🦞`) in the prompt. The error is:\n\n```\n/bin/sh: -c: line 0: syntax error near unexpected token `('\n```\n\nThis is because the emoji characters are causing shell parsing issues. But even after that error, Dean keeps responding with \"I'm here, Bobby. What's up?\" because:\n\n1. Bobby keeps saying \"Could not transcribe\" (the whisper transcription is failing)\n2. Dean gets the \"Could not transcribe\" as the message text and responds to it\n\n\n3. The conversation history keeps building with Dean saying \"I'm here, Bobby. What's up?\" repeatedly\n\nThe real problem is that whisper transcription isn't working at all, so every audio input just produces \"Could not transcribe\" as text. I need to fix the whisper transcription first, and then address the shell syntax error from those emoji characters by escaping them properly before they hit the curl command.","thinkingSignature":"74e6c2e85832a809a882a4cc98cb25e75c0a7926db34681b7d26d5746a21dc51"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nFound the problems:\n\n1. **Whisper transcription isn't working** — every recording comes back as \"Could not transcribe\"\n2. **Shell syntax error** — emoji in the prompt are breaking the curl command\n\nLet me fix both.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nj7giqo8rhfn_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Test whisper directly\necho \"test voice transcription\" | ffmpeg -f avfoundation -i \":System Audio:0\" -ac 1 -ar 16000 -t 5 -y /tmp/test_telephone.wav 2>&1 | tail -3\n# Try with a simple existing audio file first\nls ~/Desktop/Telephone/audio/*.mp3 2>/dev/null | head -3"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{