{"type":"message","id":"09c7d455","parentId":"bd03c5f8","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:19:32.270Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_linub3c8xg45_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"-rw-------  1 bobbygalletta  staff  8899 May  1 16:12 /Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/audio/reply_1777666339887.mp3\n/opt/homebrew/Cellar/openai-whisper/20250625_3/libexec/lib/python3.14/site-packages/whisper/transcribe.py:132: UserWarning: FP16 is not supported on CPU; using FP32 instead\n  warnings.warn(\"FP16 is not supported on CPU; using FP32 instead\")\n[00:00.000 --> 00:01.000]  I'm here Bobby.\n[00:01.000 --> 00:02.000]  What's up?"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":9876,"aggregated":"-rw-------  1 bobbygalletta  staff  8899 May  1 16:12 /Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/audio/reply_1777666339887.mp3\n/opt/homebrew/Cellar/openai-whisper/20250625_3/libexec/lib/python3.14/site-packages/whisper/transcribe.py:132: UserWarning: FP16 is not supported on CPU; using FP32 instead\n  warnings.warn(\"FP16 is not supported on CPU; using FP32 instead\")\n[00:00.000 --> 00:01.000]  I'm here Bobby.\n[00:01.000 --> 00:02.000]  What's up?","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777666772269}}
{"type":"message","id":"ff7ba918","parentId":"09c7d455","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:19:35.287Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Whisper works fine on existing audio files. The issue is that the audio being recorded from the browser isn't being sent to the transcription properly, OR whisper is failing on those files.\n\nLooking at the logs again: \"Could not transcribe\" - this means the server's transcription is failing. Let me check the server.js to see how it handles the audio file upload from the browser.\n\nThe server receives the audio as multipart form data. Let me check if the audio files are actually being created and if whisper is being run on them.\n","thinkingSignature":"4133cd5502862ef10f2fce5e48c1239b3e100bce6b7e2c8904be450384b5df73"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_i9zyjswpmnw6_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if whisper works on the actual recorded files\n# First check what files exist in audio dir from recording\nls -la ~/Desktop/Telephone/audio/ | grep -E \"^d|\\.webm|\\.mp4|\\.m4a\" | head -10\n# Test whisper on one of the existing reply files to confirm it works\nwhisper ~/Desktop/Telephone/audio/reply_1777666339887.mp3 --model small --language English --output_format txt --output_dir /tmp 2>&1 | tail -3"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":292,"output":247,"cacheRead":77760,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78299,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777666772277,"responseId":"06443dd4c51d57e9f8b0e5aa8baeb54f"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9551fe2b","parentId":"ff7ba918","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:19:44.435Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_i9zyjswpmnw6_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"drwx------  226 bobbygalletta  staff  7232 May  1 16:19 .\ndrwx------@  10 bobbygalletta  staff   320 May  1 16:12 ..\n  warnings.warn(\"FP16 is not supported on CPU; using FP32 instead\")\n[00:00.000 --> 00:01.000]  I'm here Bobby.\n[00:01.000 --> 00:02.000]  What's up?"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":9088,"aggregated":"drwx------  226 bobbygalletta  staff  7232 May  1 16:19 .\ndrwx------@  10 bobbygalletta  staff   320 May  1 16:12 ..\n  warnings.warn(\"FP16 is not supported on CPU; using FP32 instead\")\n[00:00.000 --> 00:01.000]  I'm here Bobby.\n[00:01.000 --> 00:02.000]  What's up?","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777666784434}}
{"type":"message","id":"663dc714","parentId":"9551fe2b","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:19:47.537Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Whisper works fine on existing MP3 files. The issue is that when Bobby talks, the audio is being recorded by the browser and sent to the server, but the transcription is returning \"Could not transcribe.\" This means either:\n\n1. The audio file isn't being saved properly\n2. The audio format is wrong\n3. The whisper command is failing silently\n\nLet me check the server logs more carefully and also check what the multipart parsing looks like. The issue might be that the audio isn't being properly extracted from the multipart form data.\n\nActually, looking at the server code I wrote earlier, the multipart parsing uses binary string splitting which can be problematic. Let me check if there are any recorded files.\n\n\nI need to examine how the server handles the multipart parsing and see if there's a mismatch between what the browser is sending and what the server expects.","thinkingSignature":"fe22a7806ce4db09d0978f1ea4038f18378b0e6e69ac31364a074a84e92a8c1f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_x3ggjy2foj21_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Look at server.js to understand multipart parsing\ncat ~/Desktop/Telephone/server.js | grep -A30 \"multipart\\|audio\\|webm\\|Content-Disposition\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":259,"output":230,"cacheRead":78048,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78537,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777666784440,"responseId":"06443de049fd689d87f6027b9da0625b"}}
{"type":"message","id":"cfa543b0","parentId":"663dc714","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:19:47.615Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_x3ggjy2foj21_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"const AUDIO_DIR = path.join(DIR, 'audio');\nconst MESSAGES_FILE = path.join(DIR, 'messages.json');\n\nif (!fs.existsSync(AUDIO_DIR)) fs.mkdirSync(AUDIO_DIR, { recursive: true });\n\nfunction saveMessages(msgs) {\n  fs.writeFileSync(MESSAGES_FILE, JSON.stringify(msgs, null, 2));\n}\n\nfunction loadMessages() {\n  if (fs.existsSync(MESSAGES_FILE)) {\n    try { return JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(MESSAGES_FILE, 'utf8')); } catch(e) {}\n  }\n  return [];\n}\n\nfunction textToAudio(text, callback) {\n  const ts = Date.now();\n  const mp3Path = path.join(AUDIO_DIR, `reply_${ts}.mp3`);\n  const aiffPath = `/tmp/dean_telephone_${ts}.aiff`;\n\n  try {\n    const clean = text.replace(/[\"\\\\]/g, '').replace(/\\n+/g, ' ').replace(/\\s+/g, ' ').trim();\n    if (!clean) { callback(null); return; }\n\n    execSync(`say \"${clean}\" -o ${aiffPath} 2>/dev/null`, { stdio: 'pipe' });\n    execSync(`ffmpeg -i ${aiffPath} \"${mp3Path}\" -y 2>/dev/null`, { stdio: 'pipe' });\n    fs.unlinkSync(aiffPath);\n    callback(mp3Path);\n  } catch(e) {\n    console.error('TTS error:', e.message);\n--\nfunction transcribeAudio(webmPath, callback) {\n  const mp3Path = webmPath.replace('.webm', '.mp3');\n  try {\n    execSync(`ffmpeg -i \"${webmPath}\" -ac 1 -ar 16000 \"${mp3Path}\" -y 2>/dev/null`, { stdio: 'pipe' });\n    execSync(`whisper \"${mp3Path}\" --model small --language English --output_format txt --output_dir /tmp 2>/dev/null`, { stdio: 'pipe' });\n    const txtPath = mp3Path.replace('.mp3', '.txt');\n    const text = fs.existsSync(txtPath) ? fs.readFileSync(txtPath, 'utf8').trim() : '';\n    callback(text || 'Could not transcribe');\n  } catch(e) {\n    console.error('Transcribe error:', e.message);\n    callback('Transcription failed');\n  }\n}\n\nconst server = http.createServer((req, res) => {\n  res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Origin', '*');\n  res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Methods', 'GET, POST, OPTIONS');\n  res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Headers', 'Content-Type, X-Since');\n\n  if (req.method === 'OPTIONS') {\n    res.writeHead(200);\n    res.end();\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Serve audio files\n  if (req.method === 'GET' && req.url.startsWith('/audio/')) {\n    const filename = path.basename(req.url);\n    const filePath = path.join(AUDIO_DIR, filename);\n    if (fs.existsSync(filePath)) {\n      res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'audio/mpeg' });\n      fs.createReadStream(filePath).pipe(res);\n    } else {\n      res.writeHead(404);\n      res.end('Not found');\n    }\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Receive audio from browser\n  if (req.method === 'POST' && req.url === '/talk') {\n    const chunks = [];\n    req.on('data', c => chunks.push(c));\n    req.on('end', () => {\n      const buffer = Buffer.concat(chunks);\n      const boundary = req.headers['content-type']?.match(/boundary=(.+)/)?.[1];\n\n      if (!boundary) {\n        // Plain JSON — fallback for simple text\n        try {\n          const { text } = JSON.parse(buffer.toString());\n          const messages = loadMessages();\n          messages.push({ from: 'user', text, timestamp: Date.now() });\n          saveMessages(messages);\n          res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n          res.end(JSON.stringify({ received: true, transcript: text }));\n          return;\n        } catch(e) {\n          res.writeHead(400);\n          res.end('Bad request');\n          return;\n        }\n      }\n\n      // Parse multipart — audio file\n      const parts = buffer.toString('binary').split('--' + boundary).filter(p => p.includes('Content-Disposition'));\n      let transcript = '';\n\n      for (const part of parts) {\n        if (part.includes('name=\"audio\"')) {\n          const fileMatch = part.match(/Content-Type:\\s*audio\\/([\\w]+)/);\n          const fileData = part.split('\\r\\n\\r\\n').slice(1).join('\\r\\n\\r\\n');\n          const ext = fileMatch ? fileMatch[1] : 'webm';\n          const audioPath = path.join(AUDIO_DIR, `recording_${Date.now()}.${ext}`);\n\n          fs.writeFileSync(audioPath, fileData, 'binary');\n\n          // Transcribe\n          transcribeAudio(audioPath, (text) => {\n            transcript = text;\n            const messages = loadMessages();\n            messages.push({ from: 'user', text: transcript, timestamp: Date.now() });\n            saveMessages(messages);\n\n            // Cleanup\n            try { fs.unlinkSync(audioPath); } catch(e) {}\n            try { fs.unlinkSync(audioPath.replace(`.${ext}`, '.mp3')); } catch(e) {}\n\n            res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n            res.end(JSON.stringify({ received: true, transcript }));\n          });\n\n          return;\n        }\n      }\n\n      res.writeHead(400);\n      res.end('No audio found');\n    });\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Get new messages\n  if (req.method === 'GET' && req.url.startsWith('/messages')) {\n    const since = parseInt(req.headers['x-since'] || '0');\n    const messages = loadMessages();\n    const newOnes = messages.filter(m => m.timestamp > since);\n    res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n    res.end(JSON.stringify({ messages: newOnes }));\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Dean posts reply\n  if (req.method === 'POST' && req.url === '/reply') {\n    let body = '';\n    req.on('data', c => body += c);\n    req.on('end', () => {\n      try {\n        const { text, fromDean } = JSON.parse(body);\n        if (fromDean) {\n          textToAudio(text, (mp3Path) => {\n            if (mp3Path) {\n              const messages = loadMessages();\n              messages.push({\n                from: 'dean',\n                text,\n                audioFile: `/audio/${path.basename(mp3Path)}`,\n                timestamp: Date.now()\n              });\n              saveMessages(messages);\n            }\n            res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n            res.end(JSON.stringify({ ok: true }));\n          });\n        } else {\n          res.writeHead(200);\n          res.end(JSON.stringify({ ok: true }));\n        }\n      } catch(e) {\n        res.writeHead(400);\n        res.end('Bad request');\n      }\n    });\n    return;\n  }\n\n  res.writeHead(404);\n  res.end('Not found');\n});\n\nserver.listen(PORT, () => {\n  console.log(`Telephone server running on port ${PORT}`);\n});"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":17,"aggregated":"const AUDIO_DIR = path.join(DIR, 'audio');\nconst MESSAGES_FILE = path.join(DIR, 'messages.json');\n\nif (!fs.existsSync(AUDIO_DIR)) fs.mkdirSync(AUDIO_DIR, { recursive: true });\n\nfunction saveMessages(msgs) {\n  fs.writeFileSync(MESSAGES_FILE, JSON.stringify(msgs, null, 2));\n}\n\nfunction loadMessages() {\n  if (fs.existsSync(MESSAGES_FILE)) {\n    try { return JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(MESSAGES_FILE, 'utf8')); } catch(e) {}\n  }\n  return [];\n}\n\nfunction textToAudio(text, callback) {\n  const ts = Date.now();\n  const mp3Path = path.join(AUDIO_DIR, `reply_${ts}.mp3`);\n  const aiffPath = `/tmp/dean_telephone_${ts}.aiff`;\n\n  try {\n    const clean = text.replace(/[\"\\\\]/g, '').replace(/\\n+/g, ' ').replace(/\\s+/g, ' ').trim();\n    if (!clean) { callback(null); return; }\n\n    execSync(`say \"${clean}\" -o ${aiffPath} 2>/dev/null`, { stdio: 'pipe' });\n    execSync(`ffmpeg -i ${aiffPath} \"${mp3Path}\" -y 2>/dev/null`, { stdio: 'pipe' });\n    fs.unlinkSync(aiffPath);\n    callback(mp3Path);\n  } catch(e) {\n    console.error('TTS error:', e.message);\n--\nfunction transcribeAudio(webmPath, callback) {\n  const mp3Path = webmPath.replace('.webm', '.mp3');\n  try {\n    execSync(`ffmpeg -i \"${webmPath}\" -ac 1 -ar 16000 \"${mp3Path}\" -y 2>/dev/null`, { stdio: 'pipe' });\n    execSync(`whisper \"${mp3Path}\" --model small --language English --output_format txt --output_dir /tmp 2>/dev/null`, { stdio: 'pipe' });\n    const txtPath = mp3Path.replace('.mp3', '.txt');\n    const text = fs.existsSync(txtPath) ? fs.readFileSync(txtPath, 'utf8').trim() : '';\n    callback(text || 'Could not transcribe');\n  } catch(e) {\n    console.error('Transcribe error:', e.message);\n    callback('Transcription failed');\n  }\n}\n\nconst server = http.createServer((req, res) => {\n  res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Origin', '*');\n  res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Methods', 'GET, POST, OPTIONS');\n  res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Headers', 'Content-Type, X-Since');\n\n  if (req.method === 'OPTIONS') {\n    res.writeHead(200);\n    res.end();\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Serve audio files\n  if (req.method === 'GET' && req.url.startsWith('/audio/')) {\n    const filename = path.basename(req.url);\n    const filePath = path.join(AUDIO_DIR, filename);\n    if (fs.existsSync(filePath)) {\n      res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'audio/mpeg' });\n      fs.createReadStream(filePath).pipe(res);\n    } else {\n      res.writeHead(404);\n      res.end('Not found');\n    }\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Receive audio from browser\n  if (req.method === 'POST' && req.url === '/talk') {\n    const chunks = [];\n    req.on('data', c => chunks.push(c));\n    req.on('end', () => {\n      const buffer = Buffer.concat(chunks);\n      const boundary = req.headers['content-type']?.match(/boundary=(.+)/)?.[1];\n\n      if (!boundary) {\n        // Plain JSON — fallback for simple text\n        try {\n          const { text } = JSON.parse(buffer.toString());\n          const messages = loadMessages();\n          messages.push({ from: 'user', text, timestamp: Date.now() });\n          saveMessages(messages);\n          res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n          res.end(JSON.stringify({ received: true, transcript: text }));\n          return;\n        } catch(e) {\n          res.writeHead(400);\n          res.end('Bad request');\n          return;\n        }\n      }\n\n      // Parse multipart — audio file\n      const parts = buffer.toString('binary').split('--' + boundary).filter(p => p.includes('Content-Disposition'));\n      let transcript = '';\n\n      for (const part of parts) {\n        if (part.includes('name=\"audio\"')) {\n          const fileMatch = part.match(/Content-Type:\\s*audio\\/([\\w]+)/);\n          const fileData = part.split('\\r\\n\\r\\n').slice(1).join('\\r\\n\\r\\n');\n          const ext = fileMatch ? fileMatch[1] : 'webm';\n          const audioPath = path.join(AUDIO_DIR, `recording_${Date.now()}.${ext}`);\n\n          fs.writeFileSync(audioPath, fileData, 'binary');\n\n          // Transcribe\n          transcribeAudio(audioPath, (text) => {\n            transcript = text;\n            const messages = loadMessages();\n            messages.push({ from: 'user', text: transcript, timestamp: Date.now() });\n            saveMessages(messages);\n\n            // Cleanup\n            try { fs.unlinkSync(audioPath); } catch(e) {}\n            try { fs.unlinkSync(audioPath.replace(`.${ext}`, '.mp3')); } catch(e) {}\n\n            res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n            res.end(JSON.stringify({ received: true, transcript }));\n          });\n\n          return;\n        }\n      }\n\n      res.writeHead(400);\n      res.end('No audio found');\n    });\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Get new messages\n  if (req.method === 'GET' && req.url.startsWith('/messages')) {\n    const since = parseInt(req.headers['x-since'] || '0');\n    const messages = loadMessages();\n    const newOnes = messages.filter(m => m.timestamp > since);\n    res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n    res.end(JSON.stringify({ messages: newOnes }));\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Dean posts reply\n  if (req.method === 'POST' && req.url === '/reply') {\n    let body = '';\n    req.on('data', c => body += c);\n    req.on('end', () => {\n      try {\n        const { text, fromDean } = JSON.parse(body);\n        if (fromDean) {\n          textToAudio(text, (mp3Path) => {\n            if (mp3Path) {\n              const messages = loadMessages();\n              messages.push({\n                from: 'dean',\n                text,\n                audioFile: `/audio/${path.basename(mp3Path)}`,\n                timestamp: Date.now()\n              });\n              saveMessages(messages);\n            }\n            res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n            res.end(JSON.stringify({ ok: true }));\n          });\n        } else {\n          res.writeHead(200);\n          res.end(JSON.stringify({ ok: true }));\n        }\n      } catch(e) {\n        res.writeHead(400);\n        res.end('Bad request');\n      }\n    });\n    return;\n  }\n\n  res.writeHead(404);\n  res.end('Not found');\n});\n\nserver.listen(PORT, () => {\n  console.log(`Telephone server running on port ${PORT}`);\n});","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777666787615}}
{"type":"message","id":"ee02df1d","parentId":"cfa543b0","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:19:54.251Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is becoming clearer:\n\n1. The browser sends audio via multipart/form-data\n2. The server parses the multipart, extracts the audio file, converts to MP3, transcribes with whisper\n3. BUT - the multipart parsing uses `buffer.toString('binary')` which can cause issues with binary data\n4. The whisper transcription itself works fine (as we tested with the reply audio)\n5. The real issue is that \"Could not transcribe\" keeps appearing\n\nWait - looking at the dean.js log, the actual transcript IS \"Could not transcribe\" - meaning whisper DID run but returned nothing useful. \n\nBUT the whisper command itself works when I test it manually on the reply audio. \n\nI think the problem might be in how the server.js handles binary data when writing the audio file. The recording files are being deleted after transcription, so I can't inspect them directly, but the pattern suggests the multipart parsing or file conversion might be corrupting the audio data before it reaches whisper. be failing silently.\n\nLet me test the transcription manually with a more robust approach and check if the audio files are being written correctly. The real issue is likely the curl command in dean.js has syntax errors from the conversation history piling up - I can see the `(` characters are breaking the shell command parsing. I need to escape the text before it gets sent to the API.\n\nLooking at the flow: the server saves messages to messages.json, dean.js reads them and sends to the OpenClaw Gateway API, then saves the response and generates TTS. The transcription is actually working (the logs show Dean saying \"I'm here Bobby, what's up?\"), but the conversation just keeps looping with the same message. That's the real problem to solve. I'm considering adding a conversation history to dean.js so it doesn't keep repeating the same greeting, but really the core issue is that Bobby's speech isn't being transcribed at all. Let me add better logging to server.js to capture what's actually happening during transcription, and maybe test the whisper command directly to see if it's working or if there's something wrong with how the audio is being passed to it. a test:\n\n```bash\n# Create a test audio file using say\nsay \"testing one two three\" -o /tmp/test_telephone.aiff\nffmpeg -i /tmp/test_telephone.aiff /tmp/test_telephone.mp3 -y\nwhisper /tmp/test_telephone.mp3 --model small --language English --output_format txt --output_dir /tmp 2>&1\n```\n\nWait - I wonder if the issue is that the recording files are being deleted BEFORE whisper finishes, or that the audio from the browser is in a format whisper can't process.\n\nLet me think about what could cause \"Could not transcribe\":\n1. whisper command fails → exception caught → callback('Transcription failed')\n2. whisper runs but returns empty text → `text || 'Could not transcribe'`\n\nThe whisper command is failing somewhere in the transcription pipeline, likely when converting the browser's webm audio to mp3 format that whisper can process. I should add some debugging to see where exactly it's breaking.\n","thinkingSignature":"0182122db7bc2ba5b40b3f8a0bffe1ab3ec8e5474b4dad4f1f52b500d84ad5ba"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\nTwo separate problems:\n\n1. **Whisper can't transcribe** — the audio from Safari isn't being converted/processed correctly before transcription\n2. **Dean keeps looping** — he's saying the same thing because the conversation history in dean.js has no memory\n\nLet me check what's actually happening with the audio files:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_sg0ulpjsvm8w_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Test whisper on a freshly made audio file\nsay \"testing the microphone on the telephone app\" -o /tmp/test_fresh.aiff\nffmpeg -i /tmp/test_fresh.aiff /tmp/test_fresh.mp3 -y 2>/dev/null\nwhisper /tmp/test_fresh.mp3 --model small --language English --output_format txt --output_dir /tmp 2>&1 | tail -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1710,"output":814,"cacheRead":78272,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80796,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777666787618,"responseId":"06443de3a0103b098857e1e69b7cbe09"}}
