{"type":"message","id":"e8657280","parentId":"f0fbb447","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:26:34.804Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me restart both services. I should also clear the messages.json to start fresh.","thinkingSignature":"d556cf3cceaf65aef5b1b4357c3a6fcbdd93ea83c6464aeef5bc17babb3ad5b6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9g4kxlq3h3lf_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Clear messages and restart\npkill -f \"dean.js\" 2>/dev/null\npkill -f \"server.js\" 2>/dev/null\nsleep 1\nrm -f ~/Desktop/Telephone/messages.json\nrm -f ~/Desktop/Telephone/.last_check\ncd ~/Desktop/Telephone && node server.js > ~/.openclaw/logs/telephone.log 2>&1 &\nsleep 1\nnode dean.js > ~/.openclaw/logs/telephone-dean.log 2>&1 &\nsleep 2\nps aux | grep -E \"server\\.js|dean\\.js\" | grep -v grep"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2022,"output":177,"cacheRead":96704,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":98903,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777667192606,"responseId":"06443f786275cb0c76f1307c07261937"}}
{"type":"message","id":"1b5931a2","parentId":"e8657280","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:26:39.217Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9g4kxlq3h3lf_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"bobbygalletta    63546   0.0  0.6 443489344  50208   ??  SN    4:26PM   0:00.10 node dean.js\nbobbygalletta    63544   0.0  0.6 443455776  48912   ??  SN    4:26PM   0:00.11 node server.js"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":4357,"aggregated":"bobbygalletta    63546   0.0  0.6 443489344  50208   ??  SN    4:26PM   0:00.10 node dean.js\nbobbygalletta    63544   0.0  0.6 443455776  48912   ??  SN    4:26PM   0:00.11 node server.js","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777667199216}}
{"type":"message","id":"1c8c33c3","parentId":"1b5931a2","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:26:45.020Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now let me test if the base64 approach works by simulating a recording in the browser and checking the transcription. But first let me verify by sending a test audio file to the server.\n","thinkingSignature":"1a75fd467cde124d096ab8b438f2c8aecda4166eca33e3314322316e0f8cf20f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jhs6nymadmw5_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Test the server with a base64-encoded test audio\nsay \"testing the new base64 system\" -o /tmp/telebase64.aiff\nffmpeg -i /tmp/telebase64.aiff /tmp/telebase64.mp3 -y 2>/dev/null\n# Convert to base64\nbase64 /tmp/telebase64.mp3 | tr -d '\\n' > /tmp/telebase64.b64\nSIZE=$(wc -c < /tmp/telebase64.b64)\necho \"Base64 size: $SIZE\"\n\n# Send to server\ncurl -s -X POST http://localhost:8791/talk \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d \"{\\\"audio\\\":\\\"$(cat /tmp/telebase64.b64)\\\",\\\"format\\\":\\\"audio/mp3\\\"}\" 2>&1 | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":270,"output":254,"cacheRead":98720,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":99244,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777667199220,"responseId":"06443f809d3891436631fc6f3f2ed058"}}
{"type":"message","id":"7721a974","parentId":"1c8c33c3","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:26:47.606Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_jhs6nymadmw5_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"base64: invalid argument /tmp/telebase64.mp3\nUsage:\tbase64 [-Ddh] [-b num] [-i in_file] [-o out_file]\n  -b, --break       break encoded output up into lines of length num\n  -D, -d, --decode  decode input\n  -h, --help        display this message\n  -i, --input       input file (default: \"-\" for stdin)\n  -o, --output      output file (default: \"-\" for stdout)\nBase64 size:        0\nNo audio or text found"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2527,"aggregated":"base64: invalid argument /tmp/telebase64.mp3\nUsage:\tbase64 [-Ddh] [-b num] [-i in_file] [-o out_file]\n  -b, --break       break encoded output up into lines of length num\n  -D, -d, --decode  decode input\n  -h, --help        display this message\n  -i, --input       input file (default: \"-\" for stdin)\n  -o, --output      output file (default: \"-\" for stdout)\nBase64 size:        0\nNo audio or text found","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777667207605}}
{"type":"message","id":"1c16a592","parentId":"7721a974","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:26:49.852Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The base64 command on macOS works differently. Let me use the correct syntax.","thinkingSignature":"b835dfda5b7d61560272e26b2269e10c39abed7e9b46238680f7e3783754b573"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_yltvfy0tssnn_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"say \"hello Bobby what is the weather today\" -o /tmp/weather_test.aiff\nffmpeg -i /tmp/weather_test.aiff /tmp/weather_test.mp3 -y 2>/dev/null\nbase64 -i /tmp/weather_test.mp3 -o /tmp/weather_b64.txt\nwc -c /tmp/weather_b64.txt\n\n# Send test\nRESULT=$(curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8791/talk \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d \"{\\\"audio\\\":\\\"$(cat /tmp/weather_b64.txt)\\\",\\\"format\\\":\\\"audio/mp3\\\"}\")\necho \"Result: $RESULT\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":365,"output":184,"cacheRead":98976,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":99525,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777667207608,"responseId":"06443f879712e4b104fe4733464f9fa7"}}
