{"type":"message","id":"1c09cdf9","parentId":"04ae5a3b","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:27:06.957Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The transcription is working now! \"Hello Bobby, what is the weather today?\" was correctly transcribed.\n\nBut there's an AI connection error: \"AI parse error: Unexpected token 'N', \"Not found\" is not valid JSON\". This means the AI endpoint at port 8787 is returning \"Not found\" - likely because dean.js is making an HTTP request but the gateway is returning a 404 or some other error.\n\nWait - the AI is actually working (transcription works), but the AI response generation is failing. Let me look at the dean.js code more carefully. It connects to port 8787 (gateway) for chat completions. But the error says \"Not found\" - maybe the path is wrong or the gateway isn't responding to the Dean.js requests properly.\n \nSo the flow is working end-to-end - dean.js successfully receives the message and the AI is generating responses - but something about how those responses are being sent back through the gateway is breaking. The transcription test shows it can work, so the issue is likely in the communication between dean.js and the gateway endpoint itself.\n","thinkingSignature":"3178e1fb5ef44cc2da2bdafdefdf6cf7bec58d4fffb6ddf2904d0a7f491a1c2e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zp4on59mh924_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Test gateway endpoint directly\ncurl -s -X POST http://localhost:8787/v1/chat/completions \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"model\":\"minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7\",\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Say hello to Bobby in 3 words\"}],\"max_tokens\":50}' 2>&1 | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":151,"output":331,"cacheRead":99520,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":100002,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timest