{"type":"message","id":"de5e6a7f","parentId":"7b5e1174","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:27:35.809Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The gateway config shows port 18789 but dean.js has 8787 hardcoded. But the original dean.js was working before - it was using `http://localhost:8787/v1/chat/completions`. Let me check what port the original dean.js was using when it successfully made AI calls.\n\nActually, the old dean.js was using 8787 and we know it was generating the \"I'm here Bobby, what's up?\" response. So 8787 WAS working at some point. The issue is that the gateway seems to have changed its port or the path has changed.\n\nLet me try checking if there's a mission-control API or if there's an OpenClaw API endpoint for chat completions. Let me look at the mission-control server that's running.","thinkingSignature":"44743ef95e096282a8eee0b0a942087f7507653dca7daed80254dfea991fc028"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uarz9oa83nxu_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check mission-control server\nlsof -i :8787 | grep LISTEN\nps aux | grep mission | grep -v grep | head -3\n# Check if the old port 8787 is the mission control server\ncurl -s http://localhost:8787/ 2>&1 | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":182,"output":244,"cacheRead":102080,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":102506,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777667252309,"responseId":"06443fb449fe25ff0f5e754467c4c281"}}
